properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 28 at 3:17AM PST until January 30 at 1:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible. Isolated gusts to 70 mph.

* WHERE...San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning, Santa Ana Mountains
and Foothills, Riverside County Mountains, San Bernardino
County Mountains and San Bernardino and Riverside County
Valleys-The Inland Empire.

* WHEN...From Wednesday morning through Thursday afternoon.
Strongest winds expected Wednesday evening into Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power
lines. Widespread power outages are possible. Travel could be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Difficult travel for high profile vehicles
especially along Interstate 15 through and below Cajon Pass,
Interstate 215 below Cajon Pass, and Interstate 10 through the
San Gorgonio Pass. .
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM WEDNESDAY MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY AFTERNOON
